Simulation Overview
Simulation will be run in Unity. The drone will be controlled through ArduPilot which uses MAVlink to communicate. Pymavlink will be used to interface with the ArduPilot MAVlink to control in addition to the Unity environment.
The simulation will be set up with five waypoints programmed in AUTO mode from ArduPilot. The obstacles at each waypoint are yet to be determined but will include packet loss, severe packet loss, intermittent connection etc. 
The AI model will monitor the telemetry data which will be trained by trail runs to predict impending signal loss. 
This will be used to monitor the drone during the mission and make optimal reactions based on what reactions reduce impending loss from the tests. 
When performing reactions the drone will enter GUIDED mode, and once impending signal loss is sufficiently low it will resume AUTO mode.
This will be validated by testing the AI tool versus drone mission without AI tools.


